list.comment: Updated the "Pay other people" cards to update both Player's banks as this was not being done before.

task.summary: Default task
Changed test cases to make the testing work more robustly
Changed test configuration methods to hopefully run properly
Added setup and teardown methods to TestPoll class
Implemented join and start listeners
Tests written for join and start
Moved message generation and sending to seperate methods
Testing didn't run for last commit so sending new commit to test previous one

ChatWindow implemented
I created the ChatWindow in tkinter to run in a separate thread. It's pretty slow so that gives Paul something to say in his part of the presentation. I made some modifications to existing code to test that the chat works, the playerRoll function can be removed later but I'm just using to ensure the chat can work as intended.
For any other tk windows (pre game windows) we won't need to thread since we won't be running them in parallel to pygame
Merge remote branch 'gui' with local branch
Static typing ftw
Added Card stub to test

I've given up using travis ci, it kept failing because of the nature of the project.
For the report: I attempted to use the Travis CI service to test the server code every time I pushed to GitHub. Despite my use of settings to allow socket addresses to be reused, the builds kept failing due to an 'Address in use' error This is because I had to keep closing and reopening the server to test various methods
Was not worth it in the end
Left out one line that made pygame not work ;)

Added __main__ to the Server folder to allow for -m running.
In fact, I have set it up so that using the -m flag to start the server is the only way it will allow. Also in this commit have added the use of both stdout and stderr to output different messages. Will update the docs on both the server and index to provide instructions on how to run the Server

Tested that all the server.send_ methods send the required message and that the messages conform to the API
Created a test client that simply inherits from socket and provides some handy methods for testing the server
Removed JSONDecodeError from TestClient as JSONDecodeError is not in Python3.4 and we also do not use that error in the TestClient anymore
Enumerate starts from 0 and was deleting messages from combined message streams
Fixed minor issues discovered on MacOS
Actually fixed errors in last commit
Made some corkonian chance and community chest cards
All chance and community chest cards are now operational :D
Upgraded the Server tests to handle doubles
Updated the "Pay other people" cards to update both Player's banks as this was not being done before.
